# Miscelaneous Functions

M00 - Programmed Stoping machine
M01 - Opcional stoping
M03 - Turn on the spindle in clockwise
M04 - Turn on the spindle in anti-clockwise
M05 - Turn spindle off without orientation, it cancel functions M03 and M04
M06 - Program Stop for changing tool
M08 - Turn on the Liquid cooling
M09 - Turn off the Liquid cooling
M17 - Turn off Sup programming
M30 - End of program, makes a total reset of the program

# Preparatory functions

Known to G functions, are a group of functions that define for the machine what to do, preparing something for operation or receive any information:

Modal Functions - Are functions that will be running for all the machine program for the next blocks, turned off only if modified by other function or by the same with different parameters.
Non Modal Functions - Are functions that everytime you need to use, they are required to be programmed, so are valid only for the block thats been running

G17 - It select the working plane that envolves X and Y axis, G17 is used as default function since the machined is turned on
G18 - It select the working plane that enmvolves X and Z axis
G19 - It select the working plane that envolvez Y and Z axis

G70 - Is Modal and programed to be used "inches" metric
G71 - Is Modal and programmed to be used "Millimeters" metric
G90 - Is Modal and programmed to use absolute cordinates 
G91 - Is Modal and programmed to use incremental cordinates

G64 - Is used for to make the machine read the movements in a continuous form, without stoping the axis between the blocks / Modal
G94 - Makes you able to control the cutting but time units for rotational movements

G54 to G57 - Are system working coordinates, what we mean by that is we can create that many "zeroed" points to work with the required part 

G60 - Is used to make exact positions/movements, so it makes "Vivid" sides, normally it makes a little fillet, and this turns that off //  Turned off by using the G64 Function

G53 - Cancel the Modal and Non-Modal Coordinates from the system / Non-Modal

# CFTCP, CFIN AND CFC Functions

This fucntions are used to cut radius

CFTCP - Convex Radius
CFIN - Concave Radius
CFC - Default

# Auxiliary Functions

N Functions - Number of blocks or sentences, this function is not obrigatory

T Functions - Are meant to select determinate cutting too, they just call the tool, it doesnt change the cutting tool so it needs to call M6 on next block ( new line )

D Functions - Are meant to call the saved diameter and compriment of the cutting tool selected and saved from 1 to 9 

F Functions - Meant to adjust cutting velocity for the cutting tool / Modal function

/ Functions - Meant to ignore the blocks that you want

; - Meant to add comments into the blocks

# - EOB meant thats the end of block, meaning that every line/block needs to finish with this caracther

#Linear Interpol

G00 + X Y Z function - is meant to make a position of the tool without making any of the cuts / Modal

G01 + X Y Z + F Function - Make rectlinear movements with any angle by the result of the coordinates writen with the Cutting speed (F)

